 \sin(2x) \geq x \qquad (0 \leq x \leq \pi/4) 
 0 = (\sin(2x) - x)' = 2\cos(2x) - 1 
 x_m = \pi/6 
 (\sin(2x) - x)'' = -4\sin(2x) \leq 0 
 \sin(2\pi/4) - \pi/4 = 1 - \pi/4 > 0 
 \pi < 4 
\operatorname{sinc} x \ge \frac{1}{2}
x \in [0,\frac{\pi}{2}]
\operatorname{sinc} \frac{\pi}{2} = \frac{2}{\pi} > \frac{1}{2}
